article.headline: Weber State 76, Montana State 59
article.story: OGDEN, Utah (AP) -- Slobodan Ocokoljic scored 20 points and was one of three Weber State players to score in double figures and the Wildcats snapped a three-game losing streak with a 76-59 victory over Montana State on Saturday. John Hamilton added 19 points and Nic Sparrow scored 12 for the Wildcats (11-12, 4-6 Big Sky), who also got their 300th all-time win at home. Montana State (13-11, 5-6) has lost six straight on the road. The Wildcats, sparked by 53 percent shooting from behind the 3-point line, broke the game open in the second half with runs of 7-0 and 8-2. The Wildcats also went 22-for-26 from the foul line, while limiting the Bobcats to just 6 of 9 free throws. Jason Erickson was the top scorer for the Bobcats with 22 points. Weber State led 32-22 at halftime thanks to a 14-0 run midway through the first half. The run was sparked by Ocokoljic's three-point play and 3-pointers by Sparrow and Hamilton. Weber State had dropped four of its last six meetings against Montana State.
